{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κάθημαι</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>κάτ-</b>, <i>2nd pers.</i> <i>singular</i> κάθησαι (<i>Ionic dialect</i> κάτ- [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.134) 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.1.6, probably in 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Sosibii Victoria” vi4, κάθῃ 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Fragmenta” 115, NT.Act.23.3, uncertain reading in “Comica Adespota” 1203, (προ-) 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Orationes” 13.171a \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>] codices; <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>singular</i> κάθηται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 597, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 35c, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 9.70, “SIG” 987.26 (Chios, 4th c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> κατέαται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.86; _imperative_ κάθησο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.191, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 627; κάθου 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 620, 4th c.BC: Anaxandrides Comicus 13, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 1017, 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 224 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κάθουσο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 11.42 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>singular</i> καθήσθω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 916 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> καθήσθωσαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 9(2).1109.38 (Thess.)\">Refs</a>]; <i>subjunctive</i> καθῶμαι, κάθῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 277, καθῆται 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 754; _optative_ καθοίμην [prev. author] “Ra.” 919, probably in [prev. author] “Lys.” 149 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>infinitive</i> καθῆσθα; <i>participle</i> καθήμενος: <i>imperfect</i> ἐκαθήμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 152, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 48.31, etc., ἐκάθητο “hymnus ad Bacchum” 14, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 510, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.6, ἐκάθησθε 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 638, ἐκάθηντο, _Ionic dialect_ ἐκατέατο variant in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.144, 8.73 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also without syllable augment καθῆστο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.569, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 1102, “Ph.” 1467, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 328c, 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 6.19, καθῆτο 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.169,217\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Ionic dialect</i> κατῆστο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.46, καθῆσθε 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.21 (with variants), καθῆντο 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 302, variant in 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.58 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> καθήατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.76 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Ionic dialect</i> κατέατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.144, 8.73, 9.90 (variant{καθ-})\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: the later <i>future</i> καθήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Lev.8.35, NT.Luke.22.30 is corrupt in 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 960 \">LXX+NT+5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>to be seated, sit</b>, αὐτός τε κάθησο καὶ ἄλλους ἵδρυε λαούς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.191; κάθησ᾽ ἑδραία 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 266 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: frequently in <i>participle</i>, πέτρῃ ἔπι προβλῆτι καθήμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.407 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπ᾽ ἀκτῆς κλαῖε κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.82; κ. οἶος ἐν Ἴδῃ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.207; ἐν ἀγῶνι κ. 23.448 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κλαῖον δ᾽ ἐν λεχέεσσι κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.497 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; θύρῃσι κ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\". 17.530; ἐπὶ ταῖσι θύραις 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 466 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αὐτόθεν ἐκ δίφροιο κ. even from his seat <b>as he sat there</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.420; καθήμεθ᾽ ἄκρων ἐκ πάγων 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 411 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκ μέσου κατῆστο <b>sate</b> aloof, remained neutral, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.83, compare 4.118, 8.73 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν θρόνῳ κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.149 \">Refs</a>]; θρόνῳ κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 315; κ. πρὸς τάφῳ [prev. author] “Hel.” 1084; πρὸς τὸ πῦρ 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 773; ἐπὶ δίφρου 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 328c; ἐπὶ τῶν ἵππων 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.5.54; ἐπὶ τοῦ ἅρματος NT.Act.8.28; ἐς τοὐργαστήριον 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.27: with _accusative_ _cognate_, ἕδραν κ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 55 \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> loci, <b>sit on</b>, ὀφρύην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 394. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> especially of courts, councils, assemblies, etc., <b>sit</b>: οἱ καθήμενοι <b>the judges, the court</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.139, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 6.3, etc.; δικαστὰς οὐχ ὁρῶ καθημένους 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 208 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὑμεῖς οἱ καθήμενοι you <b>who sit as judges</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.85; οὐκ ἐπὶ τούτῳ κ. ὁ δικαστής 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 35c; κ. ὑπὲρ τῶν νόμων 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 58.25 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the βουλή, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.43; βουλῆς περὶ τούτων καθημένης 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.116 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of an assembly, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.10.5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ κ. <b>the spectators in a theatre</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Hegesippus Epigrammaticus 1.29. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>sit still, sit quiet</b>, ὕψι περ ἐν νεφέεσσι καθημένω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.264 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; σφοῖσιν ἐνὶ μεγάροισι καθήατο (for ἐκάθηντο) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.76; ἐν πένθεϊ μεγάλῳ κατῆστο 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.46 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μετὰ κόπον κ. <b>rest</b> after labour, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 479.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: and, in bad sense, <b>sit doing nothing, lie idle</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.403, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.134 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of an army, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 9.56, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.124 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of a boat's crew, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PCair.Zen.” 107.6 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; οὐδὲν ποιοῦντες ἐνθάδε καθήμεθα, μέλλοντες ἀεί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 11.17, compare 2.23, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 142.20, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also, of an army, <b>to have its quarters, be encamped</b>, περὶ τὰς Ἀχαρνάς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.20, compare 101; ἐχθρῶν ὑπ᾽ αὐτοῖς τείχεσιν καθημένων 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 752. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>reside</b> in a place, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Neh.11.6; λαὸς καθήμενος ἐν σκοτίᾳ NT.Matt.4.16 \">LXX+NT</a>]; <b>settle</b>, εἰς Σινώπην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Musonius Philosophus “fragment” 9p.43H. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>lead a sedentary, obscure life</b>, ἐν σκότῳ καθήμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 1.83; ἔσω καθημένη 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 919 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἱ βαναυσικαὶ [τέχναι] ἀναγκάζουσι καθῆσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 4.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be engaged</b> or <b>employed</b>, especially in a sedentary business, ἐπ᾽ αὐτῷ τούτῳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.86 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἐπὶ τῇ τραπέζῃ, of bankers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 49.42, compare 45.33; ἐπ᾽ ἐργαστηρίου [prev. author] 59.67; ἐπὶ τοῦ.. ἰατρείου 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.40 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; καθῆσθαι ἐν πόλει, opposed to ζῆν ἐν Χωρίῳ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Musonius Philosophus “fragment” 11p.59H. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> <b>sit</b> as a suppliant, ἐν Δελφοῖσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.63, cf. Oracle texts [prev. work] 7.140. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3> of districts and countries, <b>lie</b>, Χωρία ὁμοίως καθήμενα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 8.8.7. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__7.b</b></Level4> <b>to be low-lying</b>, τὰ λεῖα καὶ καθήμενα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 3.1, compare “NA” 16.12 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; πεδίον κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Himerius Sophista “Orationes” 14.17 \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]; πόπανον.. κ. δωδεκόμφαλον probably <b>flat</b> in the middle, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.1367. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__8</b></Level3> of a statue, <b>to be placed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 215b, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1315b21. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__9</b></Level3> of things, <b>to be set</b> or <b>placed</b>, λαγῴοις ἐπ᾽ ἀμύλῳ καθημένοις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Teleclides Comicus 32, compare 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 108.17; τὸ πηδάλιον κ. πλάγιον 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Mechanica” 851a4, compare [prev. work] 13. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2521","accentedUnicode":"κάθημαι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1476","matchingForm":"ἑδραῖος","stepTransliteration":"hedraios","gloss":"steadfast","_zh_tw_Gloss":"定, 堅定","_es_Gloss":"firme ","_zh_Gloss":"定, 坚定"},{"strongNumber":"G2596","matchingForm":"κατά","stepTransliteration":"kata","gloss":"according to","_zh_tw_Gloss":"照著","_es_Gloss":"según","_zh_Gloss":"照着"},{"strongNumber":"G4775","matchingForm":"συγκάθημαι","stepTransliteration":"sunkathēmai","gloss":"to sit with","_zh_tw_Gloss":"一同坐, 同坐","_es_Gloss":"sentarse con","_zh_Gloss":"一同坐, 同坐"}],"shortDef":"to sit, seat, ride; to live, stay, reside","mediumDef":"to sit, seat, ride; to live, stay, reside <br /><b>to sit, be sitting,</b> <ref='Mat.9.9'>Mt. 9:9</ref>; <ref='Luk.10.13'>Lk. 10:13</ref>; <b>to be seated,</b> <ref='1Co.14.30'>1Cor. 14:30;</ref> <b>to be enthroned,</b> <ref='Rev.18.7'>Rev. 18:7;</ref> <b>to dwell, reside,</b> 